title: International day of rallies against Aboriginal community closures
text:
Topix › Pacific Travel › International day of rallies against ... International day of rallies against Aboriginal community closures 1 hr ago Read more: Green Left Weekly 
SOSBLAKAUSTRALIA held its third round of international action against Aboriginal community closures over the weekend of June 26 to 28. There were rallies in most capital cities in Australia, including Brisbane, Sydney, Melbourne, Adelaide and Perth, as well as London and Dunedin. Rallies in Sydney and Melbourne disrupted peak hour traffic due to rally goers marching through the city. Start the conversation, or Read more at Green Left Weekly.
